						March 10, 2018 at 09:13					</div>
					<div class="comment-text">
												<p>I can&#8217;t say that&#8217;s not a valid concern, mike k. But two things:</p>
<p>First, I wouldn&#8217;t lose too much sleep over what might go down at a face-to-face Trump/Kim summit, which I&#8217;d say is still more likely to not take place. </p>
<p>And wherever this leads, I credit the highly proficient DPRK negotiators with being able to suss out what Trump needs both politically and psychologically so as to make the most of whatever opportunity for progress exists.</p>
					</div>
